additional dietary protein and insulin-like growth hormone (IGF-1) Protein is essential for the body to grow and repair tissue. IGF-1 is a hormone that is produced in the body in response to the presence of protein. IGF-1 is necessary for the body to grow and repair tissue, and it also plays a role in the body’s ability to produce energy.

additional dietary protein and hip fracture There is no good evidence that suggests that consuming more dietary protein increases the risk of hip fracture. Some studies have found that diets high in protein are associated with a lower risk of hip fracture, while others have found no association.

textDelta: basic functional unit of skeletal muscle tissue A muscle fiber, also known as a muscle cell, is the basic functional unit of skeletal muscle tissue. A muscle fiber is a single cell of a muscle that contracts to produce movement.

textDelta: most common naturally-occurring form of silicon  silicon dioxide, also known as silica or quartz, is the most common naturally-occurring form of silicon. It is a hard, brittle, colorless, transparent, crystalline solid. Silicon dioxide is found in sand, clay, and granite. It is also present in the human body and is essential for the health of bones and teeth.
most common naturally-occurring form of silicon is oxide The most common naturally-occurring form of silicon is oxide.
